<h2>Adding The <i>Drafts</i> UI</h2>
<p>Though we won't complete the full functionality during this tutorial, we'll have our work cut out for us in the following article. Let's assume that for the purposes of this plugin, the&nbsp;<i>Drafts</i> UI will &nbsp;be a place where the user simply treats it like a scratch pad for ideas.</p>
<p>It may include links to articles, links to tweets, short notes about the outline, a few sentences, and so on. Generally, it serves as a "catch-all" for all of the artifacts that the author may be using throughout his or her post.</p>
<p>To that end, we're going to use a simple, single <code>textarea</code>. Furthermore, we don't want to introduce any more UI elements than are necessary so we will&nbsp;<i>not</i> be introducing a submit button. Instead, we'll save the data whenever the user clicks "Update" on the post editor.</p>
<p>That way, everything is saved all at the same time.</p>
